@startuml
' @id(SEQ-BROWSE-TREE)
' @ref(USE-BROWSE-TREE)
'
' Objective-side flow for the VSCode-style directory tree rail, with an
' alternate "group by cycle" organization (USE-GROUP-BY-CYCLE).
'
' @desc(SEQ-BROWSE-TREE, "How the left rail builds a collapsible directory tree from the model registry, with a toggle to instead group diagrams under the cycle that last touched them.")
title Browse models in a directory tree (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "ModelRegistry\n(mdd-core)" as Reg
participant "CycleRegistry\n(mdd-core)" as CReg
participant "TreeModel\n(nested nodes)" as Tree
participant "egui SidePanel\n(left rail)" as Rail

Dev -> Viewer : open viewer
Viewer -> Reg : model files
Reg --> Viewer : files (path, kind, ids)

alt organize = Directory (default)
  Viewer -> Tree : build from file paths\n(.mdd/models/<side>/<kind>/<file>)
  Tree --> Viewer : nested folder/file nodes
else organize = By cycle
  Viewer -> CReg : cycles + files touched per cycle
  CReg --> Viewer : cycle -> [files]
  Viewer -> Tree : build cycle-grouped nodes\n(Cycle N > kind > file)
  Tree --> Viewer : nested cycle nodes
end

loop each painted frame
  Viewer -> Rail : render collapsible tree\n(expand/collapse folders, selectable leaves)
  Rail --> Dev : tree rail
end

Dev -> Rail : click a diagram leaf
Rail -> Viewer : select file
Viewer -> Viewer : load_file(selected)\n(keeps existing canvas behavior)

Dev -> Rail : toggle organize mode
Rail -> Viewer : rebuild tree (other organization)
@enduml
